posts.name: The Dog House
posts.note: The Dog House is a no-frills, cash-only eatery with counter seating, offering hot dogs, burgers, pizza, and cheesesteaks. Their foot long hot dogs or two in a soft roll with some tooth and an order of French fries will fill you right up.

posts.name: Go Fish!
posts.note: Go Fish! is a casual 40-seat restaurant with British theme featuring fish 'n' chips, toffee pudding, and other eats. The dish to order is the fish and chips (French fries) with a side order of curry sauce.
posts.cptn: Fish and chips (french fries for the Americans) with a side of curry sauce. Well worth the long drive home from Go Fish in Rehobooth Beach, DE

posts.name: Hopkins Farm Creamery
posts.note: Hopkins Farm Creamery's ice cream is made with local ingredients and sold from walk-up windows on a working dairy farm. You should get their salted caramel crunch which has nuts and large chocolate chip chunks.

posts.name: Vanderwende Farm Creamery
posts.note: Vanderwende Farm Creamery's ice cream is handcrafted and made right in Bridgeville Delaware. They only use the best quality ingredients to produce a rich and creamy ice-cream. They offer a wide variety of flavors, so there is sure to be one for you.
